Issues.Body:
The [docs](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/plugins#dynamic-variants) (2nd example under "Dynamic variants" section) show this example: 

```js
matchVariant("min", (value) => `@media (min-width: ${value})`, {
  sort(a, z) {
    return parseInt(a) - parseInt(z);
  },
});
```

but when I add that same example to Tailwind Play ([here](https://play.tailwindcss.com/7jSUGQ5kjV?file=config)), I see these type linting errors:

```
(parameter) a: {
    value: string;
    modifier: string;
}
Argument of type '{ value: string; modifier: string; }' is not assignable to parameter of type 'string'.(2345)
```

```
(parameter) z: {
    value: string;
    modifier: string;
}
Argument of type '{ value: string; modifier: string; }' is not assignable to parameter of type 'string'.(2345)
```

Presumably, the example in the docs needs to be updated to use the `value` property like this:

```js
matchVariant("min", (value) => `@media (min-width: ${value})`, {
  sort(a, z) {
    return parseInt(a.value) - parseInt(z.value);
  },
});
```

